#~ msgid "<b>Connection to Discriminative Learning</b>"
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgid ""
#~ "It is instructive to contrast the "
#~ "energy-based generative objective with the"
#~ " more familiar <b>discriminative</b> objective"
#~ " used in feedforward classifiers."
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Crucially, the partition function now "
#~ "sums only over the possible labels "
#~ "$y'$ for a fixed input $\\mathbf{x}$."
#~ " This sum is typically tractable "
#~ "(e.g., over a finite set of "
#~ "classes). The intractable sum over all"
#~ " configurations $\\mathbf{x}$ is <b>not "
#~ "required</b> for discriminative training."
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgid "<b>Summary</b>"
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgid ""
#~ "<b>Energy-Based Models</b> define a "
#~ "probability distribution via $P_\\theta(\\mathbf{x})"
#~ " \\propto \\exp(-E_\\theta(\\mathbf{x}))$, linking "
#~ "low energy to high probability."
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgid ""
#~ "The learning objective is <b>maximum "
#~ "likelihood</b>, which decomposes into "
#~ "minimizing the average energy of data"
#~ " while controlling the partition function."
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgid ""
#~ "The gradient of the log-likelihood "
#~ "$f(\\theta)$ involves a <b>data term</b> "
#~ "(easy to compute) and a <b>model "
#~ "expectation</b> (intractable to compute "
#~ "exactly)."
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Learning is geometrically interpreted as "
#~ "<b>sculpting the energy landscape</b>: "
#~ "lowering basins at data points while "
#~ "raising the surrounding terrain."
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgid ""
#~ "The intractability of the model "
#~ "expectation is the central computational "
#~ "challenge that motivates approximate methods"
#~ " like <b>contrastive divergence</b>."
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgid ""
#~ "P_\\theta(\\mathbf{x}) = "
#~ "\\frac{\\exp\\left(-E_\\theta(\\mathbf{x})\\right)}{Z_\\theta}, "
#~ "\\quad \\text{where} \\quad Z_\\theta = "
#~ "\\sum_{\\tilde{\\mathbf{x}}} "
#~ "\\exp\\left(-E_\\theta(\\tilde{\\mathbf{x}})\\right)"
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgid ""
#~ "\\theta^* = \\arg\\max_\\theta \\prod_{m=1}^M "
#~ "P_\\theta(\\mathbf{x}^{(m)}) = \\arg\\max_\\theta "
#~ "\\sum_{m=1}^M \\log P_\\theta(\\mathbf{x}^{(m)})"
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgid ""
#~ "\\mathcal{L}(\\theta) = -\\frac{1}{M} \\sum_{m=1}^M"
#~ " \\log P_\\theta(\\mathbf{x}^{(m)})"
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgid ""
#~ "\\log P_\\theta(\\mathbf{x}) = "
#~ "-E_\\theta(\\mathbf{x}) - \\log Z_\\theta"
